
# PRD for GalleryGrid - A Beautiful Image Gallery Page

## Overview
GalleryGrid is a visually stunning image gallery page designed to showcase collections of images in an elegant, responsive grid layout. The page will prioritize aesthetics while maintaining high performance and usability.

## Features

### 1. Responsive Grid Layout
- Automatically adjusts to different screen sizes (desktop, tablet, mobile)
- Masonry-style layout that preserves image aspect ratios
- Dynamic column count based on viewport width (4 columns on desktop, 2 on mobile)

### 2. Image Display
- High-resolution image rendering with lazy loading
- Smooth hover effects (subtle zoom + shadow)
- Animated transitions when loading new images
- Optional lightbox/popup for full-size viewing

### 3. Filtering & Sorting
- Category filters (tags visible on hover)
- Sort by date, popularity, or custom order
- Search functionality with instant results

### 4. UI Elements
- Clean, minimalist design with ample white space
- Custom scrollbar that matches the theme
- Loading spinner during image fetch
- "Load More" button with elegant animation

## Technical Specifications

### Frontend
- HTML5/CSS3 with Flexbox/Grid
- JavaScript for interactive elements
- Optional framework: React/Vue for complex implementations
- Image optimization: WebP format with JPEG fallback

### Performance
- Lazy loading with intersection observer
- Prefetching of next set of images
- Critical CSS inlined for faster initial render

### Accessibility
- ARIA labels for all interactive elements
- Keyboard navigation support
- Proper contrast ratios for text/background

## User Flow
1. Page loads with initial set of images
2. User can scroll to trigger lazy loading
3. Clicking image opens lightbox
4. Filter/sort options appear in header
5. "Load More" appears when reaching bottom

## Design Assets
- Color palette: Pastel background with vibrant image accents
- Typography: Clean sans-serif (e.g., Inter or Poppins)
- Spacing: Consistent 16px grid system
- Icons: Minimal line icons for UI controls

## Success Metrics
- Time to First Render < 1s
- 95%+ Lighthouse score
- Average session duration > 2 minutes
- <5% bounce rate

## Future Enhancements
- Social sharing integration
- User upload capability
- AI-powered image tagging
- Dark mode toggle
